OL,3,CReform councillor under fire after
OL,4,Cvoicemail message branded racist
OL,6,FA statement from Race Council Cymru
OL,7,Fsaid that: "Offensive and racially
OL,8,Fcharged language has no place in
OL,9,Fmodern public discourse, especially
OL,10,Fwhen it comes from individuals seeking
OL,11,For holding political office. Such
OL,12,Flanguage doesn't exist in a vacuum; it
OL,13,Freflects and reinforces deep-rooted
OL,14,Fprejudices that many communities have
OL,15,Fworked hard to overcome. At a time
OL,16,Fwhen we should be striving for greater
OL,17,Finclusion and understanding, these
OL,18,Fcomments are not only unacceptable but
OL,19,Fdeeply damaging.
